{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, it explores various potential liability standards, focusing on the central role played by the concept of defect.",
    "The liability of manufacturers for damage caused by their products compensates harmed consumers.",
    "From an economic perspective, product liability is a means of controlling accident risks by incentivising adequate precautions.",
    "That is, liability induces manufacturers to improve product safety.",
    "Based on the principle of least cost avoider, liability for harm caused by AI should be allocated to the party that can most efficiently mitigate risk through their actions."
  ]
}